-- Chancellor Osborne to Give BOE Control of Mortgage Amounts, Telegraph Says
-- John Simpson
-- 2010-06-16T00:12:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-16/chancellor-osborne-to-give-boe-control-of-mortgage-amounts-telegraph-says.html

          
          
             George Osborne, the U.K. chancellor 
of the exchequer, will today disclose new controls to be given 
to the Bank of England to prevent another financial crisis, 
including the power to impose restrictions on mortgage amounts 
banks can lend, the Daily Telegraph reported without saying 
where it got the information.     
